    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Secure API Key Storage (Expo SecureStore)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mobile apps have a fundamental security constraint: the JavaScript bundle is distributed to every user's device and can be extracted. Any value baked into the bundle — including environment variables — is readable. For secrets like Anthropic API keys, you need a different strategy. This document covers the two complementary approaches: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "expo-secure-store"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for secrets the user fetches or enters at runtime, and a backend proxy for secrets that must never leave your server."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Comparison table of API key storage approaches: hardcoded, EXPO_PUBLIC_ env, AsyncStorage, Expo SecureStore, and backend proxy",
          "title": "API key storage security decision matrix"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why the Bundle is Not Safe for Secrets"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When Expo builds a release binary, it bundles your JavaScript into a single file that ships inside the APK or IPA. Any "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "EXPO_PUBLIC_"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " variable is inlined at build time — identical to hardcoding the value. Extracting it requires only:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Android — extract strings from release APK\nunzip app-release.apk assets/index.android.bundle\nstrings assets/index.android.bundle | grep sk-ant\n\n# iOS — same principle; the bundle is inside the IPA zip\nunzip MyApp.ipa && strings Payload/MyApp.app/main.jsbundle | grep sk-ant"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This takes under a minute. Any key in the bundle should be treated as public."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Expo SecureStore"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Expo SecureStore wraps platform-native encrypted storage: iOS Keychain Services and Android Keystore System. Values are encrypted at rest using hardware-backed keys, tied to the app's bundle ID, and inaccessible to other apps. It is the correct place to store tokens that the user fetches or inputs at runtime — for example, an API key the user pastes into a settings screen."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Installation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "npx expo install expo-secure-store"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The package is a native module. If you are using the Expo managed workflow, it is included in the default prebuild. For bare workflow, run "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "npx pod-install"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " after installation on iOS."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Basic Read / Write / Delete"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import * as SecureStore from \"expo-secure-store\";\n\nconst API_KEY_STORAGE_KEY = \"anthropic_api_key\";\n\n// Save a key (e.g., after user pastes it in settings)\nexport async function saveApiKey(key: string): Promise<void> {\n  await SecureStore.setItemAsync(API_KEY_STORAGE_KEY, key);\n}\n\n// Retrieve the key before making an API call\nexport async function getApiKey(): Promise<string | null> {\n  return SecureStore.getItemAsync(API_KEY_STORAGE_KEY);\n}\n\n// Delete the key on sign-out\nexport async function deleteApiKey(): Promise<void> {\n  await SecureStore.deleteItemAsync(API_KEY_STORAGE_KEY);\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "All three operations are async. There is no synchronous read. The 2 KB size limit applies to the value string — for an Anthropic API key (~60 characters) this is not a concern."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Using the Key in a Component"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import { useEffect, useState } from \"react\";\nimport * as SecureStore from \"expo-secure-store\";\nimport Anthropic from \"@anthropic-ai/sdk\";\n\nexport function useClaude() {\n  const [client, setClient] = useState<Anthropic | null>(null);\n  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    async function init() {\n      const key = await SecureStore.getItemAsync(\"anthropic_api_key\");\n      if (!key) {\n        setError(\"No API key found. Please add one in Settings.\");\n        return;\n      }\n      setClient(\n        new Anthropic({\n          apiKey: key,\n          dangerouslyAllowBrowser: true,\n        })\n      );\n    }\n    init();\n  }, []);\n\n  return { client, error };\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Settings Screen — Key Entry UI"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the user-provided key pattern is used, expose a settings screen where users can paste their own Anthropic API key. Validate the key format before saving:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "typescript"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import { useState } from \"react\";\nimport { Alert, Button, StyleSheet, Text, TextInput, View } from \"react-native\";\nimport * as SecureStore from \"expo-secure-store\";\n\nconst API_KEY_STORAGE_KEY = \"anthropic_api_key\";\nconst API_KEY_REGEX = /^sk-ant-[A-Za-z0-9_-]{80,}$/;\n\nexport default function ApiKeySettings() {\n  const [input, setInput] = useState(\"\");\n  const [saved, setSaved] = useState(false);\n\n  async function handleSave() {\n    const trimmed = input.trim();\n    if (!API_KEY_REGEX.test(trimmed)) {\n      Alert.alert(\"Invalid key\", \"Anthropic API keys start with sk-ant- and are ~100 characters long.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    await SecureStore.setItemAsync(API_KEY_STORAGE_KEY, trimmed);\n    setInput(\"\");\n    setSaved(true);\n  }\n\n  async function handleDelete() {\n    await SecureStore.deleteItemAsync(API_KEY_STORAGE_KEY);\n    setSaved(false);\n    Alert.alert(\"Removed\", \"API key deleted from secure storage.\");\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <View style={styles.container}>\n      <Text style={styles.label}>Anthropic API Key</Text>\n      <TextInput\n        style={styles.input}\n        value={input}\n        onChangeText={(v) => { setInput(v); setSaved(false); }}\n        placeholder=\"sk-ant-...\"\n        secureTextEntry   // hides characters like a password field\n        autoCapitalize=\"none\"\n        autoCorrect={false}\n      />\n      <Button title=\"Save key\" onPress={handleSave} />\n      {saved && <Button title=\"Remove saved key\" onPress={handleDelete} color=\"#dc2626\" />}\n    </View>\n  );\n}\n\nconst styles = StyleSheet.create({\n  container: { padding: 16, gap: 12 },\n  label: { fontWeight: \"600\", fontSize: 15 },\n  input: { borderWidth: 1, borderColor: \"#ccc\", borderRadius: 8, padding: 12 },\n});"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "SecureStore Options"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "setItemAsync"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "getItemAsync"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " calls accept an options object for fine-grained access control:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
